# Daily blog (Stress Free Flow website)

When the user asks for today’s blog / daily blog / a new blog post, follow this rule plus their paste brief.

## Positioning moat (every post)

- Frame Stress Free Flow as a **replacement** for people tired of wellness-subscription apps — not as “another Calm/Headspace.”
- In the **product section**, state both:
  - **Buy once:** free download; Pro is a **$4.99 one-time** unlock; no subscriptions; no ads.
  - **Privacy/native:** the **app** collects no personal data and has no in-app tracking (source of truth: `privacy.html`). Do not overclaim — the **website** may use analytics.
- Keep the guide useful first. Moat lines appear once in the product paragraph + one quiet end CTA — not as the whole article.
- Prefer exit-intent angles: subscription fatigue, sensory overload, privacy-first Apple tools, cancel/replace searches. Rotate topics so posts do not cannibalize existing `/blog` URLs or `blogs.json` titles.

## Sales-safe, not salesy

- Never frame the app or its tools as ineffective or “probably won’t help.”
- Soften clinical honesty without killing conversion: general wellness tool (not medical treatment) → practical usefulness.
- Competitor mentions: neutral or favorable to our buy-once / Apple-only / tactile / no-ads positioning. Never praise competitors in a way that makes SFF look lesser.
- No hype, urgency, fake scarcity, emoji spam, or hard-sell language.
- CTA once near the end: free download → try tools → unlock Pro once ($4.99) if useful.

## Product facts (verified only)

- Apple devices only (iPhone/iPad); App Store; built in Swift/Xcode.
- Free download; Pro = one-time $4.99; no subscriptions; no ads.

## Write + wire

- Match recent posts: meta, canonical, OG/Twitter, BlogPosting + BreadcrumbList JSON-LD, sticky CTA, related reads, sources/disclaimer, footer, `nav-menu.js` + `sticky-cta.js`, current `styles.css?v=`.
- Create `/blog/[slug].html`; add top entry in `blogs.json`; add URL to `sitemap.xml`; add to `blog.html` topic directory; bump `blog-feed.js?v=` on `blog.html` and `index.html` if needed.
- Update homepage “Start here” only if the post earns a top-3 slot.
- Outbound links: authoritative and sales-upward (NIMH, NCCIH, Apple Support, reputable explainers). Do not link pages that discourage wellness apps or say these tools are a waste.
- Internal links: 2–4 related blog posts + homepage/App Store CTA.

## Publish

- After wiring, commit only relevant files and push to `origin/main` (see deploy-live rule).
- Reply with the live URL and suggest a hard refresh.
